author: COMSOL
description: This model simulates a tank with an asymmetrically positioned impeller. The tank and impeller geometry are defined using parts from the Mixer Module Part Library. A liquid is continuously fed into the tank near the top and exits through an outlet at the bottom. The turbulent flow field resulting from the impeller agitation is solved for using a frozen-rotor analysis. The model shows how to visualize the mixing and compute the residence-time distribution using particle tracing. A pulse containing 50,000 massless particles is injected and tracked as it flows through the mixer. The residence-time distribution is computed by counting the number of particles that have reached the outlet.
